.TH NICX 1 "2025-04-25" "nicx 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
nicx \- personal Linux system toolkit by Nicolas
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nicx
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ subcommand ]
.RI [ options ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nicx
is a personal Linux system toolkit designed for use on minimal or fresh Linux
installations. It provides a unified CLI for system inspection, configuration
management, and Linux administration tasks.
.PP
The tool is self-contained, requires no runtime dependencies beyond the C++
standard library, and stores its configuration in
.I ~/.config/nicx/config.toml
following the XDG Base Directory specification.
.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B system
Inspect the current system. Default subcommand is
.BR info .
.TP
.B help
Show general help, or help for a specific command when given as an argument.
.TP
.B version
Print the version string and exit.
.
.SH SYSTEM SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B nicx system info
Display a full system overview including:
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
Operating system name, ID, version, kernel, hostname, and init system
.IP \(bu
CPU model, architecture, core count, and thread count
.IP \(bu
Memory total, used, available, and swap usage
.IP \(bu
Boot mode (EFI/BIOS), bootloader detection (GRUB, systemd-boot, rEFInd)
.IP \(bu
Disk partitions with filesystem, usage, and LUKS encryption status
.RE
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI color output (also respected when stdout is not a TTY).
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B nicx
reads its configuration from
.I ~/.config/nicx/config.toml
(or
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nicx/config.toml
if the XDG variable is set). The file is created with defaults on first run.
.PP
.B Example config.toml:
.PP
.RS
.nf
[output]
color = true
# format = terminal

[system]
# show_swap = true
.fi
.RE
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/nicx/config.toml
User configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/nicx
Default install location when using the install script.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/nicx
System-wide install location when using
.BR "make install" .
.
.SH INSTALLATION
Install system-wide from source:
.PP
.RS
.nf
git clone https://github.com/microservice-tech-nicolas/nicx
cd nicx
make install
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or install to
.I ~/.local/bin
without root:
.PP
.RS
.nf
make install PREFIX=~/.local
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or use the one-line installer:
.PP
.RS
.nf
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/microservice-tech-nicolas/nicx/main/scripts/install.sh | sh
.fi
.RE
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show full system information:
.B nicx system info
.TP
Show help for the system command:
.B nicx help system
.TP
Show version:
.B nicx --version
.
.SH EXTENDING
.B nicx
uses a self-registering command pattern. Adding a new command requires only
creating a new translation unit with a static
.B CommandRegistrar
— no changes to existing infrastructure. See the project README on GitHub for
the developer guide.
.
